<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-5887] Unexpected behavior when combining onException and multiple adviceWith in camel-core</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-5887</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Here is the unit test with 3 tests (expected results and the strange behavior) : &lt;a href=&quot;http://pastebin.com/JUnLFy70&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://pastebin.com/JUnLFy70&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A second adviceWith() on a second route will change the behavior from the first route during an Exception.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;adviceWith is only used once per route, as suggested in the recommendation : &lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.apache.org/advicewith.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.apache.org/advicewith.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;It is recommended to only advice a given route once (you can of course advice multiple routes). If you do it multiple times, then it may not work as expected, especially when any kind of error handling is involved. The Camel team plan for Camel 3.0 to support this as internal refactorings in the routing engine is needed to support this properly.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
